ms in both their first and second language; the effects of multimedia and visualization techniques on learners’ comprehension and retention of L2 idioms; students’ misinterpretations of L2 idioms; L2 learners’ comprehension of creative idiom variants and their use of idioms in free composition writing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexIdioms. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxSwedish speakers. 0aLanguage acquiusition. 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aSwedish languagexIdioms. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aL2 idiom comprehension.  aSLA.  aidiom misinterpretation.  aidiom use in composition writing.  aidiomatic expressions.  aidioms.  alanguage learning.  asecond language acquisition.  asecond language comprehension.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishz978311061030708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066146040uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178892237140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781788922371423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781788922371/original  a978-3-11-061030-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066146-0  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PP